	<text>
		<body>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>June 6 1854</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Revd Sir. </p>	
			<p rend="indent(2)">I enclose the proceedings of<lb/> the Congregation Shearith Israel&#44; at a Meeting<lb/> held on <date>4th</date> inst. for publication in your<lb/> <sic>invalueable</sic> Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">The interest you have always<lb/> felt in the proceedings of the various Conrega&#45;<lb/>tions&#44; induces this Congregation to forward the<lb/> same to you&#44; in order to show&#44; that notwith&#45;<lb/>standing all efforts used&#44; particularly in this<lb/> City&#44; to ridicule the Orthodox Congregations&#44;<lb/> &#38; to destroy our sacred Religion&#44; Shearith<lb/> Israel is in a flourishing condition&#44; and<lb/> enabled to contribute to the establishment<lb/> of an Orthodox Synagogue.  Trusting that<lb/> He&#44; whose hand has always been <sic>outstreched</sic><lb/> over <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; will still continue <add>to</add> do so&#44; to<lb/> those who trust in the God of <persName>Abraham</persName>&#44; and<lb/> adhere to ancient landmarks of Judaism.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With my best wishes for your prospe&#45;<lb/>rity&#44; I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Revd Sir   yr obt Sr</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">B Paleature<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Secty K K S. I.</p>
			
